This paper discusses generalization in reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the conceptual properties of RL benchmarks and how they differ from those in supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also touches on state representation and model architecture, which are relevant to natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), so cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses challenges and future lines of research, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
